      "question": "A circular pizza of radius $14$ $cm$ is cut into $8$ equal sectors. The area of each sector is:",
      "answer": "(A)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "The area of a circle with radius $r$ is given by $A = \\pi r^2$.",
          "Using $r = 14$ $cm$ and $\\pi = \\frac{22}{7}$, the total area is $A = \\frac{22}{7} \\times 14 \\times 14 = 616$ $cm^2$.",
          "Since the pizza is cut into $8$ equal sectors, the area of each sector is the total area divided by $8$.",
          "Area of one sector $= \\frac{616}{8} = 77$ $cm^2$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$A_{total} = \\pi r^2 = \\frac{22}{7} \\times 14 \\times 14 = 22 \\times 2 \\times 14 = 616 \\text{ cm}^2 \\\\ A_{sector} = \\frac{A_{total}}{8} = \\frac{616}{8} = 77 \\text{ cm}^2$"
      },
